BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:All is Calm: The Christmas Truce of 1914
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261202T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261202T210000
DTSTAMP:20260724T154921Z
UID:occ-374@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Peter Rothstein's a cappella retelling of the WWI Christmas tr
 uce\, built from soldiers' letters and period songs.\n\nOn Christmas Eve 1
 914\, soldiers along the Western Front laid down their rifles\, crossed no
 -man's land\, and sang together. Peter Rothstein's documentary-style music
 al tells that true story through trench songs\, patriotic tunes\, and caro
 ls\, sung a cappella and woven with the soldiers' own words from letters a
 nd journals. Music by Erick Lichte and Timothy C. Takach. Presented by The
  Atlanta Opera as part of its Discoveries series.
GEO:33.757035;-84.389486
LAST-MODIFIED:20260724T154831Z
LOCATION:Theatrical Outfit\, 84 Luckie St NW
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.theatricaloutfit.org/whats-on/all-is-calm-the-christmas-tr
 uce-of-1914/book/63801/
END:VEVENT
