BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Tosca
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270501T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270501T221500
DTSTAMP:20260724T154921Z
UID:occ-401@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Opera
DESCRIPTION:Puccini's melodrama of a diva\, her painter lover\, and Rome's
  predatory police chief\, sung in Italian.\n\nPuccini's 1900 melodrama of 
 jealousy\, torture\, and betrayal\, set in Rome in June 1800 with Napoleon
 's army on the march. The singer Floria Tosca and her painter lover Cavara
 dossi run afoul of Scarpia\, the city's chief of police\, who wants Cavara
 dossi dead and Tosca for himself. Musicologist Joseph Kerman famously dism
 issed it as a 'shabby little shocker\,' yet it remains among the most perf
 ormed operas anywhere\, its score carrying 'Vissi d'arte' and 'E lucevan l
 e stelle.' Presented by the Atlanta Opera.
GEO:33.88471;-84.4585962
LAST-MODIFIED:20260724T154831Z
LOCATION:Cobb Energy Performing Arts Centre\, 2800 Cobb Galleria Pkwy
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://tickets.atlantaopera.org/145983/145984
END:VEVENT
